Overview

Models the meta-data for a specific object's properties. Can be used to read and write properties using strings as property names. Obtained by calling runtime_properties() on an object.

See Also

  • Object::runtime_properties()


Properties

Methods

clear()

No action - only present to satisfy the List aspect of this class.


count().Int32

Returns the count of how many properties this object has.


get( Int32 property_index ).RuntimeProperty

Returns meta-data about the specific property at the given property_index (0..<count).


get( String name ).RuntimeProperty

Returns meta-data about the specific property with the given name, or "null" if there's no such property.


to_String().String

Returns a list of the properties tracked by this object as a String.


type_name().String (inherited)

Returns the true class name of this object. Implemented by the runtime; you should not override this method. Equivalent to calling "runtime_type.name" in the introspection library.

Example: 

 local Object obj = "Hello World"
 println( obj.type_name ) # prints: String
